        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 29 at 2:57PM EDT until April 29 at 4:00PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>SVRDTX

The National Weather Service in Detroit/Pontiac has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
East central Oakland County in southeastern Michigan...
Central Macomb County in southeastern Michigan...

* Until 400 PM EDT.

* At 257 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Rochester, or
near Troy, moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

* This severe thunderstorm will be near...
Rochester, Troy, and Sterling Heights around 300 PM EDT.
Macomb Township and Clinton around 305 PM EDT.
New Baltimore around 315 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include
Rochester Hills, Shelby Township, Ray Center, Utica, Washington,
Auburn Hills, Bloomfield Hills, New Haven, Stoney Creek Metro Park,
and Chesterfield Township.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
